.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Pottes","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Rafael, Ana, Enrique, Luis, Manuel, Abdiel, Alejandro, Andres, Bernarda, Eduvigis, Emilia, Eulalia.","Catalan: from the plural of <i>porta</i> ‘door, gate’ (see   Porta  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Porta","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jorge, Carlos, Jose, Edmundo, Eduardo, Mario, Alfonso, Bolivar, Carols, Felino, Francisco, Ignacio.  Italian Aldo, Angelo, Pio, Vito, Cosmo, Giulio, Salvatore, Siena.","Italian, Catalan, Aragonese, Galician, French, German, and Jewish (Sephardic): topographic name for someone who lived near the gates of a fortified town (and often was in charge of them; thus in part a metonymic occupational name), from <i>porta</i> ‘gateway, door, entrance’ (from Latin <i>porta</i> ‘door, entrance’). Compare   Laporta  ."]}]},{"name":"Thierry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Germanic <i>Theodoric</i>, composed of elements meaning ‘people’ and ‘rule’.  Compare  <b>Terry</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thierry Seigneur de Pottes was born in 1260, in Pottes, Hainaut, Belgium, his father, Gerard De Pottes, was 30 and his mother, Alexandra  Rieulay de Douai, was 10. He married Marie de Leschelle in 1289. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 3 daughters. He died in 1305, at the age of 45."},"et":{"1260–1305":"1260–1305","1295–1342":"1295–1342","1275–1305":"1275–1305","1282–Female":"1282–Surnud","1290–1342":"1290–1342","1305–Female":"1305–Surnud","1306–Male":"1306–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1230–1300":"1230–1300","1250–13